    "uses": "Allopurinol is commonly prescribed for patients suffering from gout, as it helps to prevent painful gout attacks by reducing uric acid levels. Additionally, it is used in the treatment of certain types of kidney stones, particularly those associated with high uric acid. It can also be beneficial for patients undergoing chemotherapy, as it helps to mitigate the increase in uric acid levels resulting from tumor lysis syndrome.\n\nIn the context of chronic kidney disease, Allopurinol plays a significant role in controlling hyperuricemia. By managing uric acid levels, it may also help to reduce the risk of cardiovascular complications associated with elevated uric acid levels. Overall, this medication is an essential part of therapy for individuals with conditions related to uric acid metabolism and is available in oral and injectable forms.",
